description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Midwife&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assessment Date: &lt;span&gt;M&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;onday &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;7&lt;/span&gt;th&lt;span&gt; December 2020 at 10:00 AM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Please be expected to be available all day on assessment day).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for enthusiastic midwives to join the highly motivated midwifery team within UCLH, we have very strong Trust values of Safety, Kindness, Teamwork and Improving and we strive to live and example these in our everyday work with women and with our colleagues.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have modern and well equipped facilities, excellent investment in staff education and development and a strong research culture across maternity services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We promote normality, have a rising number of women seeking to use our birth centre and have increased local home birth numbers. We aim to deliver high quality and safe care at all times.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our posts at this level are rotational to give experience in all areas of the service, and to ensure that all midwives grow and maintain their full range of clinical skills and technical knowledge.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Midwives who join this team will have the opportunity for clinical rotation into all areas of our maternity service over time, to maintain and develop their wider clinical skills including an opportunity to work in a case loading team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are a midwife who would like to be a part of our future and can meet this challenge we welcome your interest in a post with us – please apply today!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: &lt;span&gt;15&lt;/span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anna White anna.white5@nhs.net or Ana Esquerdo ana.esquerdo@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
